{"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"read"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"buffer","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sv","text":"UnsafeMutableRawPointer"},{"text":"!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"count","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gssize","preciseIdentifier":"c:glibconfig.h@T@gssize","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"title":"read(buffer:count:cancellable:)","externalID":"s:3GIO19InputStreamProtocolPAAE4read6buffer5count11cancellableSiSvSg_SiAA14CancellableRefVSgtKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO18FileInputStreamRefV","extendedModule":"GIO","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInputStreamRef\/read(buffer:count:cancellable:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/fileinputstreamref\/read(buffer:count:cancellable:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInputStreamRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInputStreamRef\/InputStreamProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Tries to read "},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" bytes from the stream into the buffer starting at","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"buffer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Will block during this read."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"read","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"buffer"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafeMutableRawPointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sv"},{"text":"!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"count","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"? = nil) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:glibconfig.h@T@gssize","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gssize"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If count is zero returns zero and does nothing. A value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"larger than "},{"code":"G_MAXSSIZE","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will cause a ","type":"text"},{"code":"invalidArgument","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" error."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On success, the number of bytes read into the buffer is returned.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is not an error if this is not the same as the requested size, as it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can happen e.g. near the end of a file. Zero is returned on end of file"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(or if "},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is zero),  but never otherwise."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The returned "},{"code":"buffer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is not a nul-terminated string, it can contain nul bytes"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"at any position, and this function doesn’t nul-terminate the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"buffer"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", then the operation can be cancelled by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"triggering the cancellable object from another thread. If the operation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"was cancelled, the error ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancelled"},{"text":" will be returned. If an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operation was partially finished when the operation was cancelled the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"partial result will be returned, without an error.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On error -1 is returned and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":" is set accordingly."}]}]}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/FileInputStreamRef":{"abstract":[{"code":"GFileInputStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" provides input streams that take their","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"content from a file.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"FileInputStreamRef"}],"title":"FileInputStreamRef","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"FileInputStreamRef"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/fileinputstreamref","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInputStream